clinical_study.brief_title: Prospective Evaluation of Proteinuria and Renal Function in Non-diabetic Patients With Progressive Renal Disease
clinical_study.official_title: Randomised, Double-blind, 52-wk, Parallel-grp Multicentre, PIIb Study to Evaluate Effects of Rosuvastatin 10mg, Rosuvastatin 40mg and Atorvastatin 80mg on Urinary Protein Excretion in Hypercholesterolaemic Non-diabetic Patients With Moderate Proteinuria

brief_summary.textblock: The purpose of this study is to evaluate the effects of Crestor (rosuvastatin) and (Lipitor) atorvastatin on urinary protein excretion over 1 year in non-diabetes with moderate proteinuria and hypercholesterolaemia.

study_design_info.masking: Quadruple (Participant, Care Provider, Investigator, Outcomes Assessor)

primary_outcome.description: Urinary protein/creatinine ratio (mg/g) =urine protein concentration (mg/dL)/ urine creatinine concentration (g/dL). Outcome measure is the ratio of Week 52 [LOCF] urine protein/creatinine ratio over baseline urine protein/creatinine ratio.

secondary_outcome.measure: Urinary Protein/Creatinine Ratio at Week 26.
secondary_outcome.description: Urinary protein/creatinine ratio (mg/g) =urine protein concentration (mg/dL)/ urine creatinine concentration (g/dL). Outcome measure is the ratio of Week 26 urine protein/creatinine ratio over baseline urine protein/creatinine ratio.

secondary_outcome.measure: Urinary Albumin/Creatinine Ratio at Week 26
secondary_outcome.description: Urinary albumin/creatinine ratio (mg/g) =urine albumin concentration (mg/dL)/ urine creatinine concentration (g/dL). Outcome measure is the ratio of Week 26 urine albumin/creatinine ratio over baseline urine albumin/creatinine ratio.

secondary_outcome.measure: Urinary Albumin/Creatinine Ratio at Week 52 [LOCF]
secondary_outcome.description: Urinary albumin/creatinine ratio (mg/g) =urine albumin concentration (mg/dL)/ urine creatinine concentration (g/dL). Outcome measure is the ratio of Week 52 [LOCF] urine albumin/creatinine ratio over baseline urine albumin/creatinine ratio.

secondary_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline in Estimated Glomerular Filtration Rate (eGFR) at Week 26
secondary_outcome.description: The change from baseline in eGFR at Week 26 is the Week 26 value minus baseline value.

secondary_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline in eGFR at Week 52 [LOCF]
secondary_outcome.description: The change from baseline in eGFR at Week 52 [LOCF] is the Week 52 value or last observation carried forward minus baseline value.

secondary_outcome.measure: Correlation of Changes From Baseline in Urinary Protein/Creatinine Ratio With Percent Change From Baseline in Total Cholesterol [TC] at Week 26.
secondary_outcome.description: Correlation of changes from baseline in urinary protein/creatinine ratio with percent change from baseline in lipids and lipoprotein concentrations at Week 26. (Correlation values range from -1 to +1. -1 indicates a perfect negative linear relationship while a +1 indicates a perfect linear positive relationship. A value of zero indicates no relationship.)

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- greater than or equal to 18 years of age
- Hyperlipidemia
- Urinary protein
Exclusion Criteria:
- Previous rosuvastatin treatment < 6 months prior to Visit 1
- Statin intolerance
- Severe hypertension
- Diabetes

participant_flow.recruitment_details: 797 patients entered the study with moderate proteinuria and hypercholesterolemia and were receiving stable treatment with angiotensin converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitors and/or angiotensin receptor blockers (ARBs) for 3 or more months prior to Visit 1. The study was conducted at 114 participating centers in 11 countries.
participant_flow.pre_assignment_details: 237 patients [pts] completed the 8-week lead-in period and were randomized.
